This paper deals with optimal coding over a noisy communication channel, which is a classic problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of feedback to improve the error exponent is also a well-studied topic in information theory, and this paper specifically focuses on the case of noisy feedback, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of linear coding schemes, which is a common topic in network information theory (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different coding schemes, which can be analyzed using machine learning techniques (cs.MM) and statistical learning theory (cs.LG).
